snippet.textDisplay:
The author is really good at writing and developing realistic relationships, dynamics and human feelings. I really like this long journey Endeavor is experiencing into becoming a better person.
You don't have to forgive past negative actions someone did against you or your family but accept that the person in front of you is no longer the person who hurt you in the past. Only that way can someone leave behind the emotional shackles that are keeping them from making new lasting bonds with others and living life to its fullest.

snippet.textDisplay: One thing that you surely have felt but you have not realized, is that unlike Deku's fights, in which you know that he cannot die because he is the main character, here you do not know what will happen. Endeavor could have died upon receiving the first attack on his face, but he surprises you by striking himself with his flames, even though he can't move. Finally, when he ascends to the sky, you don't know if he has sacrificed himself and died in his own flames, and it's not until the music changes and he poses gloriously that we can catch our breath. That is why this is the best battle of season 4.
snippet.textOriginal: One thing that you surely have felt but you have not realized, is that unlike Deku's fights, in which you know that he cannot die because he is the main character, here you do not know what will happen. Endeavor could have died upon receiving the first attack on his face, but he surprises you by striking himself with his flames, even though he can't move. Finally, when he ascends to the sky, you don't know if he has sacrificed himself and died in his own flames, and it's not until the music changes and he poses gloriously that we can catch our breath.
